  "name": "Peanut Allergy - Peanut-Specific IgE Lab Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find peanut-allergic patients via peanut-specific IgE antibody measurements. LOINC 6206-7 (Peanut IgE Ab in Serum). Threshold: any positive (>0.35 kU/L = sensitization). Includes Path C patients (peanut-IgE positive without formal peanut allergy diagnosis \u2014 sensitized but not yet coded).",
  "prompt": "Find patients with positive peanut-specific IgE antibody lab results.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with positive peanut IgE.",
    "broad": "Find patients with positive peanut-specific immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibody measurements \u2014 indicating sensitization to peanut allergen.",
    "expert": "Search Observation resources with LOINC 6206-7 (Peanut IgE Ab in Serum). The peanut Synthea module records IgE values in 1-100 kU/L range for sensitized patients. Query: Observation?code=http://loinc.org|6206-7"
  },
